The health sector can probably be pardoned for not seeing the pandemic coming.But still, this is no excuse for the ministry’s lack of preparation to have enough equipment to avert unforeseen emergencies.  If there is anything that the Covid-19 pandemic has exposed, it’s our lack of preparedness. From our health sector to learning institutions, we have been put to the test.
Unfortunately, we still cannot tell the early warning signs of a crisis. We still lag behind in aligning our systems, which is meant to work for us, not against us.



